FBIS4-57207 "drlat094_p_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-094 Daily Report 13 May 1994 Ecuador Workers Report on Injuries Workers Report on Injuries PA1405004794 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 13 May 94 PA1405004794 Quito Voz de los Andes Spanish BFN [From "The Voz Andes Newscast"] [Excerpt] Union leaders reported that at least five IESS employees were injured in a clash with police when they were protesting government plans to privatize the IESS. A union leader said the injuries were inflicted by members of the security forces during an act of brutal repression in which tear gas and police sticks were used. I want to express my strong condemnation of this criminal repression, the leader said. Five of our fellow workers were injured solely for the crime of defending social security, he added. [passage omitted]
